JOHANNESBURG Bidvest is mapping out an ambitious expansion plan outside South Africa, seeking deals amounting to billions of rands. Bidvest CEO Lindsay Ralphs says the company is raising funds to make international acquisitions.They re looking to the UK for new profit streams, raising their war chest to about $1-billion (R13,27bn).Bidvest says overseas purchases will help protect it from rand volatility.The rand lost nearly half its value against the dollar in the three years through 2015, before gaining 13 percent last year.Other local firms making purchases abroad include clothing retailer Foschini Group and investment company, Brait. eNCA